$ SQLite shell: .show
@ .show

The SQLite shell command `.show` reports the values for some settings such as col- and row separator, the filename of the opened database etc.

code {
sqlite> .show
        echo: off
         eqp: off
     explain: auto
     headers: off
        mode: list
   nullvalue: ""
      output: stdout
colseparator: "|"
rowseparator: "\n"
       stats: off
       width:
    filename: ./foobar.db
code }

sa:
  â†’ development/databases/SQLite/shell
